DoTs are useless if they are magic based, they dispel easy and anyone with common sense on a pvp server keeps dummy slot open.<br>
Poison/Disease DoTs resist very easy, and so infrequent that carrying a few potions should take care of them.<br>
Pets are the most useless of all, low resists and AI.<br>
<br>
MELEE rules pvp. Though it is easy to avoid being hit, a skilled melee will still be able to stick to and kill a caster so long as he has sufficient defenses to last and endure through any spells. Very easy to do in the real game... high 50's/60.<br>
It comes down to what melee is the best, simple answer... HYBRID. As Sanaleb said earlier.<br>
No class is ultimate and all will suffer losses, thats all there is to it.<br>
