<br>
--PvE-- <br>
There's no easier class to level 1-50+ solo.  There are other classes that can solo as well if not better at different level ranges, but bards can solo consistently well all the way from 1 to 50+.  Keep in mind, I didn't say they solo easily, the bard is one of the most demanding classes you can play, however, bards can solo *well* when played well (i.e. AE dot kiting 8-9 mobs at a time, all without losing any mana). Moreover, at later levels bards can do wonders for raiding and exping groups.<br>
<br>
--PvP--<br>
Bards are badass **PvP outdoors** 50+ (I say outdoors because indoors bards are average at best, and I say PvP because a bard's own damage output is too low to make them great PK's in most circumstances, sometimes charm can change things though). The one class that even well-equipped and well-played bards will struggle against is the VERY well-played enchanter, and because the enchanter is also a demanding class, most 50+ enchanters on PvP servers have skillz.  Pallies and Warriors in good gear can be nearly impossible to kill without charm, but they don't present a real threat outdoors anyway.  I've never had the opportunity to fight a ranger with endless quiver skill, a badass bow and arrow, and the horse that aids rangers in bow usage, but I imagine that would be a tough fight as well, one a bard probably couldn't win if the horse is nearly as fast as the bard (I've heard speed varies quite a bit and that the fastest horses are comparable to a high level selos with a magical drum, but I don't have any personal experience with any of the upper end horses). HOWEVER, a well-played well-equipped ranger without a horse and endless quiver will die to a well-played, well-equipped bard outdoors if the ranger really wants to stay and fight (so please don't say &quot;bards just run around&quot; anyone that's fought a good bard outdoors knows that while a bard can run and recover a bard can also do enough damage to kill someone). Also, at later levels bards can again do wonders for pvp groups outdoors (ever seen 3 or 4 rogues/monks/shadowknights/rangers supported by a bard engage another group, all the melee's sporting bard selos, haste and resists or regen? it's ugly :P).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=weewackiwoohoo>weewackiwoohoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 11:32:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Golem Wands</span><hr size=1> Clamor,<br>
<br>
Overall your point is well taken, but it's not exactly true. Since you can't cast those 2 instacast buffs while mezzed/stunned, they won't always prevent you from getting stripped by pumice/cancel magic/bard debuffer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaranna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 12:52:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yoink, golem wand conversation now~</span><hr size=1> Clammor- from what I've seen on RZ, a mage with a pet up is a bloody mean beast in pvp, especially at high levels, not a sucky class at all.  With either the nasty epic pet, or the (backstabbing) water-pet, a mage can harass the heck out of you, in many cases enough to kill you.  In an outdoor zone, try facing an epic mage pet with velocity up.  Stop to root the pet and the mage nukes you- stop to mez it, the mage nukes you- your only chance is having a bard in group to run you away from the pet (velocity &gt; SoE).  In a dungeon, the only way to escape a mage pet is to run around, train half the zone possibly, as well as yourself and the mage.  Certainly tactics PB favoured from what I saw (Trylun/Tyvenn know what I refer to), but not tactics you would choose for honourable pvp on RZ.  Just for the record I'm not a mage(I'm a cleric), but my room-mate has played one for years, and I've helped a bit :P<br>
<br>
Without a doubt, SKs are the best solo pvp class in EQ (all things being equal).  Harmtouch is merely an excuse people make most of the time- the majority of the SK's damage is done with taps and melees- HT is just to stop them running.  I've seen Reddog kill 4 players at once without going near HT - (though his unholy steed and primal 2H helped a bit :P).  A necro with a pet up is nothing to sniff at either, the pet nips at your ankles while the DoTs hurt.  <br>
<br>
Nuking a necro is useless, taps are just way too efficient- they are very vulnerable to a smart opponent just clicking top-slot and pumicing themselves of the DoTs.  I don't include manaburn wizzies there, simply because their &quot;high-skilled pvp&quot; consists of clicking their manaburn hotkey, mod, gate, and /afk in bazaar until burn pops again.  A handful of these nasty gank-gaters roamed rallos for a while, disgraceful imho.  <br>
<br>
Druids are great too- nice combination of DoTs, nukes and efficient heals- SoE makes them darn near impossible to kill outdoors.  Rangers are scary in pvp with a Tantor's + tracking...in an outdoor zone they'll find you fairly quickly.  Only truly bad pvp classes at higher levels are BL's (though no one's played one enough to really see), clerics (sigh) and shamans- with 80+PR/DR they'll never land a painful dot on you, their nukes are hopelessly inefficient vs. healing classes- solo pvp they're puny imho.  Monks are the devil to avoid in a dungeon, and at high levels their damage output shames even rogues :P<br>
<br>
Best support class in pvp (though it pains me to say this as a cleric) is easily a bard- indoors or outdoors.  Having seen Fathom and Lohengrin team up with a rogue and spank  numerous pks outdoors, they're an obvious choice.  Second I would put enchanters- tash, rapture, blind, cripple, root- player ready to be killed.  Or mez/nuking if you can get the timing right, pretty scary.  Clerics come a lowly third, though no one owns a non-manaburn wizzy like us ^_^<br>
<br>
Taranna Dhossarim <br>
60 Cleric of Tunare, Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utassthegreat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tass the great</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 4:26:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yoink, golem wand conversation now~</span><hr size=1> monk shame an equal equipped and level rogue? LMFAO!! <p>DISCLAIMER:<BR>This is my opinion.  As such, it should not be taken as fact even though I believe it to be so.  Everyone is entitiled to thier own opinions and as much of a voice to them as is given me.  Please do not judge my words too harshly.  They are only my words and as such, are only as powerful as you make them.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzyronote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyronote</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 9:31:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yoink, golem wand conversation now~</span><hr size=1> Speaking of Rogues there is a nice heated discussion on EQDiva, where everyone (wit IS a bard site afterall =) thinks no matter what a Bard will own a rogue. I have beaten a few at higher levels than me, and lost to none. Maybe a PvP server is different, but I do not see anything that would be different in a 1v1 duel, other then perhaps some additional assistance. Sure, Bards can outrun Rogues, but when they fire up their DoT or DD, they will get one pulse if that before the Rogue is on your ass again. And I agree with a statement earlier 'bards only run', this is the only FACT I have seen yet =) <p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="0">
