<br>
First, I don't see any posts here that have claimed bards own rogues under all circumstances, always (my comments were regarding OUTDOORS and 50+), but I haven't seen the eqdiva postings you are talking about so maybe such a claim was made there.  Anyone that thinks a bard is going to own a good rogue indoors is completely off base.  More than likely the rogue will waste the bard unless the rogue can be mezzed, in which case the bard will just melee the rogue until he gets low, mez the rogue and heal to full while he does do, then continue this same cycle til the rogue runs or dies.  Anyone, such as yourself, that seems to think a rogue can own a bard outdoors is equally off base.  Lvl 12+ a well-equpped, well-played bard &gt; well-euipped well-played rogue outdoors. Your assumption that bards can only sing one song at a time is the problem (and leads me to question how the hell you've leveld a bard up to 16).  Bards can twist up to 4 songs consistently (although lag and RL dexterity usually permit only 3), which means when they are running around a rogue and start to cast a dot (I have in mind single target long-range dots from lvls 30, 38, and 46, rather than AE dots, since you have to be in melee range to use those so it doesn't matter if the bard has selos up or not, he'll have to get in range or the rogue) or a dd (bellow), bards don't lose selos and slow down so that the rogue can somehow instantly catch up.  As a matter of fact, at 49+ bards only have to twist selos once every 2.5 minutes. The only way a rogue can kill someone is to keep them in melee range or try to use a bow on a runner.  Since a bard can do a lot more damage to you out of melee range, and a bard can stay out of melee range easily outdoors, bards &gt; rogues outdoors 12+, but especially more so as you approach 50+.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Clammor,<br>
<br>
You still claim mezz is insufficent to allow for buff strippage with bard debuff/pumice and anything else that removes less than 4 buffs at one go.  Your reasoning seems to be that wizzies will have some dummy slots before instacast buffs and then crappy buffs before their real buffs.  First, most people are too lazy to do that unless they know what's coming, but to be fair to your point, its true that at higher levels most people constantly check who is in zone so that they do know what's coming.  Nevertheless even with the ideal buff scheme you describe, a bard using the 1 buff at a time strip song can still strip a wizzie if they can land mezz.  First, if there are dummy slots, a bard can fill them with unresistable songs, like occuslion of sound (which also lowers MR), the faction song (which has no effect on PC's but still leaves an icon), or bellow even, which isn't unresistable but is damn close and also leaves an icon for some reason. Once those slots are filled, when the bard lands mezz it will be at the back of all the buffs.  The bard can then just twist mezz and debuff to remove one buff at a time until the wizzie is compeletly stripped.  An enchanter can just fill the dummy slost with tash and some other debuff, not they they need a wizzie mezzed to stip one anyway. Alternatively, if the wizzie is able to yonder off and get enough time to proc epic rune on self it's true that can be difficult for most classes to overcome, but again, it's not **impossible**.  A bard or enc would just mezz and mana drain and then dispell it again and nuke/beat oom wizzie to death.  Even if the wizzie is able to reapply, if he can't get out of zone he'll still die.  I'm not arguing here that wizzies with epics are easy kills (I don't think anyone in their right mind would that's actually fought an epic wizzie).  Wizzies are one class I'm always on my toes around outdoors, and a class I wouldn't even bother messing with indoors if I had the choice.  However, you essentially claimed that it's **impossible** to srip a wizzie without golem wands or a chanter's pillage, and it's that claim that is false.<br>
<br>
Also, as a melee chasing a caster around with the intent pumice them during a nuke so they can't cast instacast buffs, you usually stop to cast as the wizzie starts to cast, and usually the wizzie won't start casting til they've gotten out of melee range, which means the wizzie usually won't be able to melee to interupt pumice casting.  Moreover, melees with maxxed skills fighting other melee's still miss alot of the time. I've never had a wizzie try to melee me 20+, but I imagine they'd miss a lot more. Also, and I'm not completely sure whether this applies to casters or not, in my own experiences as a pure melee you can't melee while you cast something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utyvenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyvenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/28/02 7:29:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.broadpark.no/~bsvenhe/tyvimg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yoink, golem wand conversation now~</span><hr size=1> Clammor on RZ now the only thing wizards do is...<br>
